Mr. Song approved of it,
so take care of that for me.

251
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:24,585
I'll talk to Mr. Song
about the budget myself.

252
00:17:24,668 --> 00:17:25,836
What?

253
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,297
Hey, Mr. Song already gave me
his consent--

254
00:17:28,380 --> 00:17:30,549
I'll proceed with it
once I check with Mr. Song.

255
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:36,597
My gosh, this little punk.

256
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:38,849
Mr. Lee.

257
00:17:42,269 --> 00:17:44,271
I know you and Tae-jun are close.

258
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:45,981
But watch what you tell him.

259
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:47,858
You don't want to lose your job, do you?

260
00:17:57,493 --> 00:17:59,453
Ask the Ministry of Strategy and Finance
and the Ministry of Labor

261
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:01,830
-if they checked the bill.
-Yes, ma'am.

262
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:04,458
Show me the bill
on the outplacement for women.

263
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:06,168
Ms. Kang.

264
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:10,214
-How did the meeting go?
-The committee put our bill on hold.

265
00:18:10,297 --> 00:18:12,549
And Mr. Song
didn't even attend the meeting.

266
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,264
Where's Mr. Song?

267
00:18:19,348 --> 00:18:21,266
It'll be useless for you to go see him.

268
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:24,770
Apparently, Mr. Song and Mr. Jo
had a one-on-one meeting last night.

269
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:26,897
They must've struck a deal.

270
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,440
No wonder something felt so off.

271
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:32,152
How did it go with Mr. Jo?

272
00:18:35,531 --> 00:18:37,950
He's not the type of man to back down.

273
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:39,910
I should sort things out.

274
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:42,704
I need to go somewhere.

275
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:49,086
I just got a call from Mr. Oh again

276
00:18:49,169 --> 00:18:51,130
-about the expressway--
-I said, get rid of it!

277
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:54,091
Okay, I'll do that.

278
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:57,094
ASSEMBLYWOMAN KANG

279
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,474
I'm sorry about that. Just get rid of it.

280
00:19:02,558 --> 00:19:03,684
Yes, sir.

281
00:19:08,272 --> 00:19:10,774
What the heck do they want me to do?

282
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:15,779
What? Why are you staring at me?

283
00:19:24,371 --> 00:19:25,205
Mr. Jang.

284
00:19:27,624 --> 00:19:28,667
Let's talk outside.

285
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:37,217
Mr. Jo wants to bring me down in return
for letting Mr. Song become the minister?

286
00:19:40,387 --> 00:19:41,930
I'm a pretty valuable hostage, aren't I?

287
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,515
So what now?

288
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:47,603
-What's your plan?
-Let's wait for a little while.

289
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,771
You can propose the bill again

290
00:19:50,063 --> 00:19:52,274
-once he becomes the minister.
-What about after that?

291
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:57,112
Mr. Song will be the Minister of Justice
who has control over the prosecutors.

292
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:59,698
Mr. Jo will be the floor leader
who has control over the party.

293
00:19:59,781 --> 00:20:01,325
Who will be able to deal with them then?

294
00:20:03,327 --> 00:20:04,912
Waiting isn't going to make a difference.

295
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:08,457
Seon-yeong.

296
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:10,876
Don't get involved.

297
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,545
This is my fight.

298
00:20:13,629 --> 00:20:15,505
You could really get hurt.

299
00:20:15,797 --> 00:20:17,341
Mr. Song will be the one getting hurt.

300
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:20,928
I'm going to be a thorn in his side.

301
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:25,641
See you later, ma'am.

302
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:26,892
RICE CAKES

303
00:20:26,975 --> 00:20:28,894
Excuse me, young man.

304
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:30,646
Yes, ma'am.

305
00:20:32,731 --> 00:20:35,984
Are people like me allowed
to attend the hearing as well?

306
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:43,659
Up until a few days ago,

307
00:20:44,618 --> 00:20:48,580
I used to sell stuff over there
with my grandson.

308
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:51,375
If it weren't for my grandson,

309
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:54,294
I wouldn't have been able
to work for so long.

310
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:57,339
He would always come
and stay by my side after school

311
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,466
and help me sell stuff.

312
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,718
What a kind grandson.

313
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:03,804
Yes, he's very kind.

314
00:21:05,013 --> 00:21:06,556
He grew up with no parents.

315
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,850
But he's still
the kindest person on earth.

316
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:14,481
After he graduated from high school,
he wanted to start his own business.

317
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:17,359
So he leased and renovated a store.

318
00:21:17,442 --> 00:21:18,610
But the landlord

319
00:21:19,528 --> 00:21:21,780
sold the store in just two months.

320
00:21:24,366 --> 00:21:25,325
He was so upset

321
00:21:26,326 --> 00:21:28,912
that he cried for days and nights.

322
00:21:29,496 --> 00:21:32,124
Now he's working at a factory
because he doesn't want

323
00:21:32,207 --> 00:21:33,750
to burden me.

324
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:39,172
So tell me.

325
00:21:39,548 --> 00:21:40,549
If I attend this hearing,

326
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,926
will I be able to work

327
00:21:43,552 --> 00:21:44,845
with my grandson again?

328
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:52,644
I can't guarantee anything.

329
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:55,022
But it might help you find some solutions.

330
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:58,859
There's a very competent chief of staff
working in our office.

331
00:21:59,359 --> 00:22:02,529
If you explain your situation to him,
I'm sure he'll help you out.

332
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:06,325
Is he that competent?

333
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:08,160
Of course, ma'am.

334
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:18,587
ASSEMBLYWOMAN KANG

335
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:20,380
Is the Judiciary Committee meeting over?

336
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:24,801
Yes, I got a call
from Chairperson Lee earlier.

337
00:22:24,885 --> 00:22:26,428
He did what you asked.

338
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:32,476
Mr. Song, you should be more supportive
of Chairperson Lee.

339
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:35,187
If he finds out you made a deal
with Mr. Jo over the floor leader--

340
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:36,396
Just play dumb for now.

341
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:38,607
If he finds out now,
it won't do us any good.

342
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:39,858
Okay, sir.

343
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:41,526
My goodness, that feels nice.

344
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:42,819
-Press harder.
-Okay, sir.

345
00:22:42,903 --> 00:22:45,739
I haven't even officially
become the minister yet.

346
00:22:45,822 --> 00:22:48,366
Why are there so many people
asking me for favors already?

347
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:51,244
My goodness, my shoulders are killing me.
That feels nice.

348
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:53,538
Mr. Song, it's been so long.

349
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:54,873
Yes, it has. Hello.

350
00:22:54,956 --> 00:22:57,459
My gosh, things are so hectic these days.

351
00:23:00,003 --> 00:23:02,839
-This will feel refreshing.
-My goodness, that's nice.

352
00:23:08,678 --> 00:23:09,596
Ms. Kang.

353
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:18,146
I'm sorry. I know how hard you worked
to make that bill.

354
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:19,898
There's no need for you to be sorry.

355
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:22,609
This isn't the first time
our bill got stomped on like this.

356
00:23:23,985 --> 00:23:26,446
We can't just stand still
just because our bill got stomped on.

357
00:23:28,406 --> 00:23:29,825
We need to get ready to fight back

358
00:23:31,326 --> 00:23:33,370
to make sure it doesn't get
stomped on again.

359
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:43,630
Hello, Ms. Jeong Eun-hui.

360
00:23:44,756 --> 00:23:46,383
This is Assemblywoman Kang Seon-yeong.

361
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:54,391
He's been in there for ages.

362
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,685
He's reading the bill
from Mr. Jo's office, right?

363
00:23:56,768 --> 00:23:57,727
Yes.

364
00:23:58,311 --> 00:24:00,480
Why does he care so much about their bill?

365
00:24:05,485 --> 00:24:06,695
Mr. Jang.

366
00:24:07,612 --> 00:24:09,197
Here are the files on Seobuk Market.

367
00:24:14,035 --> 00:24:15,120
Hye-won.

368
00:24:16,913 --> 00:24:19,916
-Yes?
-Keep an eye on Ms. Kang's office.

369
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,335
Tell me if you notice anything.

370
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:25,172
Should I know what this is about?

371
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:31,136
No.

372
00:24:31,678 --> 00:24:33,638
Okay, I'll let you know.

373
00:24:44,524 --> 00:24:47,819
The water supply and sewerage system here
is too old, and the river smells very bad.

374
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:49,863
So 60 percent of the residents
had already agreed

375
00:24:49,946 --> 00:24:51,865
to the redevelopment
before you got elected.

376
00:24:51,948 --> 00:24:53,992
Once Seobuk Market
starts getting redeveloped,

377
00:24:54,075 --> 00:24:55,368
the same thing will happen here.

378
00:24:55,952 --> 00:24:57,913
But this area only needs to deal

379
00:24:57,996 --> 00:25:00,290
with the river
and the water supply and sewerage system.

380
00:25:00,373 --> 00:25:01,875
Well, yes.

381
00:25:02,751 --> 00:25:05,921
But the residents and merchants
want the area to get redeveloped.

382
00:25:06,004 --> 00:25:08,173
The city is in a pickle because of that.

383
00:25:12,677 --> 00:25:16,389
That can't be a reason
to kick these people out of their homes.

384
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:18,683
But they're going
to carry out the execution soon.

385
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,352
Yes, you're right.

386
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,771
The public hearing
only causes people to fight.

387
00:25:22,854 --> 00:25:24,898
I'm not sure how it'll turn out this time.

388
00:25:29,110 --> 00:25:31,821
-Ma'am, let us help you.
-No, it's okay.

389
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:33,240
-Give her a hand.
-Yes, sir.

390
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:39,537
Joojin Chemical's affiliate

391
00:25:39,621 --> 00:25:42,666
is part of the redevelopment, right?

392
00:25:42,749 --> 00:25:44,459
Yes, it's Joojin Constructions.

393
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:50,632
I heard you're concerned these days

394
00:25:50,715 --> 00:25:53,009
because you reported Mr. Song

395
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:55,220
to the ethics committee of our party.

396
00:25:55,804 --> 00:25:57,931
I did report him,
but you know how it works.

397
00:25:58,014 --> 00:26:00,642
The head commissioner
is in support of Mr. Song.

398
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:03,061
I'm very concerned about what I should do.

399
00:26:03,144 --> 00:26:06,398
-The party isn't very happy with it.
-If you're not going to cancel the report,

400
00:26:06,481 --> 00:26:07,774
I'd like to help you out.

401
00:26:08,566 --> 00:26:12,362
That'd be great for me.
But it could put you in a tight spot.

402
00:26:12,445 --> 00:26:14,990
I'll help you out as long
as you're okay with it.

403
00:26:16,199 --> 00:26:18,201
But the head commissioner--

404
00:26:18,285 --> 00:26:20,078
He might be able to put out a small fire,

405
00:26:21,746 --> 00:26:23,707
but he won't be able to put out a big one.

406
00:26:28,545 --> 00:26:29,462
Mr. Jang.

407
00:26:31,798 --> 00:26:34,592
Apparently, Ms. Kang
met up with Ms. Jeong.

408
00:26:36,344 --> 00:26:39,431
She also contacted the assemblywomen
of the opposition party and ours.

409
00:26:39,514 --> 00:26:41,141
I think Ms. Kang is planning

410
00:26:41,224 --> 00:26:44,602
to report Mr. Song
to the National Assembly Ethics Committee.

411
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,479
Where is Ms. Kang right now?

412
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:49,107
She's in a meeting with the Ministry
of Gender Equality and Family.

413
00:26:50,317 --> 00:26:51,151
Okay.

414
00:27:08,501 --> 00:27:12,255
Now that we're done
discussing the lone-parent project,

415
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:14,507
I'd like to start talking
about the National Assembly.

416
00:27:14,591 --> 00:27:16,926
Assemblyman Song's offensive comment
toward women

417
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:19,929
has become quite an issue recently.

418
00:27:20,013 --> 00:27:20,847
Assemblywoman Kang.

419
00:27:20,930 --> 00:27:24,017
You're planning to report him
to the National Assembly Ethics Committee?

420
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:26,644
Yes. I'm going to report him
to the committee

421
00:27:26,728 --> 00:27:28,772
for violating Article 146
of the National Assembly Act

422
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:32,275
which prohibits making insulting comments
at the National Assembly.

423
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,735
Many assemblywomen from both

424
00:27:33,818 --> 00:27:36,279
the ruling and opposition party
have agreed to participate.

425
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:37,739
I see.

426
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:40,950
Offensive comments toward women
have become a global issue these days.

427
00:27:41,034 --> 00:27:43,161
Is there a reason why
it can be more of a problem when

428
00:27:43,244 --> 00:27:45,121
such comments
are made by an assembly member?

429
00:27:45,205 --> 00:27:47,374
Assembly members are people who make laws.

430
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:49,626
They have an obligation to be fair.

431
00:27:49,709 --> 00:27:52,462
They shouldn't make comments
that could encourage discrimination.

432
00:27:52,545 --> 00:27:54,672
Thus, the right punishment
and disciplinary action

433
00:27:54,756 --> 00:27:57,550
need to be taken against assembly members
who make such comments.

434
00:27:57,634 --> 00:27:59,928
I'm hoping this will warn people

435
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:03,390
about making offensive comments
on all kinds of issues.

436
00:28:10,772 --> 00:28:12,649
You could really get hurt.

437
00:28:12,899 --> 00:28:14,442
Mr. Song will be the one getting hurt.

438
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:18,029
I'm going to be a thorn in his side.

439
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:25,537
With the lead of Assemblywoman Jeong
of the Daehan Party,

440
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,747
twenty assemblywomen
reported Assemblyman Song

441
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,165
to the National Assembly Ethics Committee

442
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:31,960
for having made an offensive comment
toward women.

443
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:34,170
-The assemblywomen of both parties
-Won-sik.

444
00:28:34,254 --> 00:28:37,173
-Hand me the toner.
-filed a request to the executive office

445
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:39,175
-to take disciplinary action
-Here you go.

446
00:28:39,259 --> 00:28:40,969
-against Assemblyman Song.
-That's enough.

447
00:28:41,052 --> 00:28:43,138
In the worst-case scenario,

448
00:28:43,221 --> 00:28:44,514
he might even end up resigning.

449
00:28:44,597 --> 00:28:46,349
Once the request reaches the committee,

450
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:50,520
-it will cause a controversy
-Gosh, it's so hard to become a minister.

451
00:28:50,603 --> 00:28:54,065
as to whether he's qualified to become
the next Minister of Justice.

452
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:57,235
We're getting tons of phone calls
from the press.

453
00:28:57,736 --> 00:28:59,738
Find out all the assemblywomen
who participated.

454
00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:01,197
And prepare for a press conference.

455
00:29:01,614 --> 00:29:02,657
Mr. Jang.

456
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:07,620
Do you think Mr. Song will be satisfied
with just a press conference?

457
00:29:08,455 --> 00:29:10,623
-What?
-You should put yourself

458
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:12,250
before Ms. Kang for now.

459
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:16,838
If you don't stop Ms. Kang,

460
00:29:16,921 --> 00:29:19,132
you'll end up losing everything.

461
00:29:19,758 --> 00:29:22,427
You've recently come back
from the district office.

462
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:25,054
If you keep hesitating,

463
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:28,683
we can't guarantee
what move the assemblyman will make next.

464
00:29:33,646 --> 00:29:34,939
Yes, Mr. Song.

465
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:40,612
The most severe disciplinary action that
the National Assembly Ethics Committee...

466
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:54,751
You startled me.

467
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:58,087
My goodness, the buzzing sound
really gets on my nerves.

468
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:08,181
Are you not going to do anything?

469
00:30:08,264 --> 00:30:10,391
Not only one but two assemblywomen
are after me.

470
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:16,231
Is there a thing between you and Ms. Kang?

471
00:30:16,314 --> 00:30:18,024
No, sir. There's nothing.

472
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:20,151
Then why are you hesitating?

473
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:22,946
Sir, let me take care of this.

474
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:24,531
-I'll--
-I'll take care of it.

475
00:30:25,949 --> 00:30:27,075
How?

476
00:31:05,822 --> 00:31:07,991
UIGWANG CITY HALL

477
00:31:08,074 --> 00:31:09,367
PUBLIC HEARING ON THE REDEVELOPMENT
OF UIGWANG AND SEONGJIN CITY

478
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:11,202
WITHDRAW THE REDEVELOPMENT PLAN

479
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:12,912
My goodness.

480
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:14,414
WITHDRAW THE REDEVELOPMENT PLAN

481
00:31:14,497 --> 00:31:16,165
WE ARE AGAINST
POSTPONING THE REDEVELOPMENT

482
00:31:16,249 --> 00:31:18,835
-There are a lot of people.
-What a relief.

483
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:21,671
-Let's sit over there.
-There?

484
00:31:21,754 --> 00:31:22,839
Yes.

485
00:31:26,467 --> 00:31:27,760
-Ma'am.
-Yes?

486
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:29,345
Wait here. I'll get you a drink.

487
00:31:29,429 --> 00:31:30,471
-Thanks.
-Okay.

488
00:31:32,348 --> 00:31:33,558
Is Mr. Hwang not here?

489
00:31:33,641 --> 00:31:36,185
Why isn't he here yet?
He said he'd be here.

490
00:31:44,235 --> 00:31:46,237
They're going to pass
Ms. Kang's bill today, right?

491
00:31:46,321 --> 00:31:50,199
Yes, but I got a call earlier
saying the bill got postponed.

492
00:31:50,283 --> 00:31:51,826
-Really?
-Yes.

493
00:31:52,452 --> 00:31:54,370
-How come?
-Hello, Mr. Lee.

494
00:31:55,663 --> 00:31:59,208
Hey, you even came to the public hearing?
You're working very hard.

495
00:32:01,377 --> 00:32:02,545
Mr. Lee, this is for you.

496
00:32:03,463 --> 00:32:06,716
You didn't have to spend money.
I should be the one buying this.

497
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:08,676
Is Mr. Jang not here?

498
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,471
He'll come as soon
as he takes care of something urgent.

499
00:32:11,554 --> 00:32:12,972
I see.

500
00:32:13,848 --> 00:32:16,309
PUBLIC HEARING ON THE REDEVELOPMENT
OF UIGWANG AND SEONGJIN CITY

501
00:32:16,392 --> 00:32:18,186
-Thanks for this.
-No problem, sir.

502
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:23,775
Okay, bye.

503
00:32:26,069 --> 00:32:27,904
Ms. Kang, Ms. Jeong just withdrew

504
00:32:27,987 --> 00:32:30,740
the report on Mr. Song from
the National Assembly Ethics Committee.

505
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,677
Ms. Jeong, I heard you canceled--

506
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:53,179
You came just in time.
I was just about to call you.

507
00:32:53,805 --> 00:32:54,806
What happened?

508
00:32:54,889 --> 00:32:56,599
I feel like it's too risky of a move.

509
00:32:56,683 --> 00:32:59,102
The other assemblywomen
also agree with me.

510
00:32:59,185 --> 00:33:01,604
I won't forget how much you helped.

511
00:33:01,688 --> 00:33:03,231
I need to go to a meeting now.

512
00:33:03,314 --> 00:33:04,983
Wait, Ms. Jeong.

513
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:07,694
Ms. Kang.

514
00:33:07,777 --> 00:33:11,364
Let's not make this a big gender issue.

515
00:33:12,156 --> 00:33:14,283
The society is already complicated
as it is.

516
00:33:27,255 --> 00:33:30,091
This is a letter of dismissal
as a spokesperson. Please sign it.

517
00:33:30,675 --> 00:33:31,884
Tae-jun!

518
00:33:31,968 --> 00:33:34,846
If she refuses, she'll also be dismissed
from the Environment and Labor Committee.

519
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:36,180
What? Dismissed?

520
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:38,099
Just accept it.

521
00:33:38,182 --> 00:33:40,309
Then I'll find a new position for you.

522
00:33:40,393 --> 00:33:42,687
-Come outside!
-Will you please excuse us?

523
00:33:42,770 --> 00:33:44,313
-Ms. Kang, I'll--
-Mr. Go.

524
00:33:57,785 --> 00:33:59,287
Who's the new spokesperson?

525
00:34:01,372 --> 00:34:02,415
Ms. Jeong?

526
00:34:06,502 --> 00:34:07,795
Go and tell Mr. Song this.

527
00:34:07,879 --> 00:34:10,631
He'll get hurt as much as I do.

528
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:12,467
-Seon-yeong.
-Don't give up on your dream.

529
00:34:14,093 --> 00:34:15,344
I won't give up on mine either.

530
00:34:15,428 --> 00:34:16,929
I'll protect both my dream and you.

531
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:19,390
This is the best option. Please trust me.

532
00:34:20,433 --> 00:34:21,392
I did trust you.

533
00:34:22,602 --> 00:34:23,770
Up until now, that is.

534
00:34:24,353 --> 00:34:25,772
Then keep trusting me!

535
00:34:36,365 --> 00:34:37,658
Do you have to take it this far?

536
00:34:39,243 --> 00:34:42,288
Take good care of Ms. Kang
before things get worse.

537
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,249
Tae-jun!

538
00:34:45,958 --> 00:34:48,127
Hello, everyone. I hope this goes well.

539
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,218
Hello, everyone.

540
00:34:55,968 --> 00:34:58,805
I'm Jeong Eun-hui, and I've been
appointed as the spokesperson

541
00:34:58,888 --> 00:35:00,056
for the Daehan Party.

542
00:35:00,139 --> 00:35:01,432
DAEHAN PARTY EXECUTIVE OFFICE

543
00:35:01,516 --> 00:35:04,227
I feel a great sense of responsibility
for taking on an important duty

544
00:35:04,519 --> 00:35:06,270
in such an important time.

545
00:35:07,188 --> 00:35:09,565
I will do my best to make sure
the people of our country

546
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:11,901
will be able to love and trust our party
more than before.

547
00:35:11,984 --> 00:35:14,403
I will fulfill my duty

548
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,405
-as the spokesperson
-Just accept it, ma'am.

549
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:17,657
Even the bill got postponed.

550
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:18,991
If you also get dismissed from--

551
00:35:19,075 --> 00:35:21,869
Then that will end my term
as an assemblywoman.

552
00:35:21,953 --> 00:35:23,162
I will communicate a lot more.

553
00:35:23,538 --> 00:35:26,290
Unjust condemnations will be dealt
with harsh criticism.

554
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:28,584
And logical criticism will be dealt
with realistic and...

555
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:34,006
Did you take care of it?

556
00:35:34,423 --> 00:35:36,342
You don't look so happy.

557
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:44,517
Mr. Jang, I have everything ready
for the public hearing.

558
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:47,145
-Where's Mr. Song?
-He just left.

559
00:35:47,228 --> 00:35:49,772
Bring the rest of the materials.
I'll see you there.

560
00:35:50,356 --> 00:35:51,315
Okay.

561
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:56,612
-He works at Uigwang City Hall.
-I see.

562
00:35:56,696 --> 00:35:58,906
-I'm sorry for being late.
-You must be busy.

563
00:35:58,990 --> 00:36:01,450
We're grateful that you came.

564
00:36:01,951 --> 00:36:03,828
The hearing has just begun.
Let us go inside.

565
00:36:03,911 --> 00:36:05,705
-This way, please.
-Sure.

566
00:36:09,208 --> 00:36:10,042
You said this project

567
00:36:10,126 --> 00:36:12,128
should be implemented
for the sake of this community.

568
00:36:12,211 --> 00:36:14,839
But how can a project
that disregards its people

569
00:36:14,922 --> 00:36:16,048
do good for their community?

570
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:18,384
They can't do business elsewhere
during the construction,

571
00:36:18,467 --> 00:36:19,719
and the rent will increase.

572
00:36:19,802 --> 00:36:22,471
You know that these merchants
can't return here.

573
00:36:22,555 --> 00:36:25,308
Did you begin this project
to kick out the merchants

574
00:36:25,391 --> 00:36:27,143
-and to increase the rent?
-Why is he here?

575
00:36:27,226 --> 00:36:30,438
The redevelopment
also involves Seongjin City.

576
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:32,190
He probably wants to have a say.

577
00:36:32,273 --> 00:36:34,567
If you call this is a win-win situation,

578
00:36:34,650 --> 00:36:36,444
you probably don't know
what that phrase means.

579
00:36:36,986 --> 00:36:39,322
-Do not proceed without an alternative.
-Ma'am.

580
00:36:39,405 --> 00:36:41,073
-You must
-The man on the left

581
00:36:41,157 --> 00:36:43,117
-persuade them first.
-is the man I talked about.

582
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:44,744
I suggest that you proceed

583
00:36:44,827 --> 00:36:48,664
-after you come to an agreement.
-He's repeating textbook lines.

584
00:36:49,165 --> 00:36:50,833
He's going to mention the rent.

585
00:36:50,917 --> 00:36:53,586
If we establish a regulation
to prevent an increase in the rent

586
00:36:53,669 --> 00:36:55,796
and let the landlords and tenants
sign an agreement,

587
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:58,841
we can drop the rent increase
from ten percent to five percent.

588
00:36:58,925 --> 00:37:01,761
We already decided to do this.
Why should we stop it?

589
00:37:01,844 --> 00:37:03,429
-You all agreed!
-He's right.

590
00:37:03,512 --> 00:37:05,598
Why do you think we've waited until now?

591
00:37:05,681 --> 00:37:08,184
We couldn't repair our building
because of the redevelopment

592
00:37:08,267 --> 00:37:10,561
-even when our roofs leaked.
-They want us to lower the rent

593
00:37:10,645 --> 00:37:12,647
and fix the building because it's too old.

594
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:15,524
-We lost so much money like that!
-We couldn't even do business!

595
00:37:15,608 --> 00:37:19,070
-We're just trying to survive together!
-You have to let the community live!

596
00:37:19,153 --> 00:37:21,364
-Enough gambling with the compensation!
-What?

597
00:37:21,447 --> 00:37:22,406
The compensation?

598
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:25,243
What's the point
of preparing for the hearing?

599
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,036
The public hearing is a mess.

600
00:37:27,119 --> 00:37:29,330
-Stop saying that!
-Let us go, Mr. Song.

601
00:37:29,413 --> 00:37:31,165
I said that's not the case!
What's with you?

602
00:37:31,249 --> 00:37:33,125
They asked us to lower the rent

603
00:37:33,209 --> 00:37:35,378
and be considerate.
Do you know how much we suffered?

604
00:37:35,461 --> 00:37:36,921
What? What did you say?

605
00:37:37,004 --> 00:37:39,590
Is it our fault that this is happening?

606
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:41,050
We have to make a living also!

607
00:37:58,025 --> 00:38:00,778
It looks like Mr. Oh planned this.

608
00:38:00,861 --> 00:38:03,239
I found this
as I looked over the budget...

609
00:38:03,322 --> 00:38:04,865
for Seoul and Uigwang Expressway.

610
00:38:15,751 --> 00:38:17,128
Yes, Mr. Hwang.

611
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:19,505
The public hearing is going smoothly.

612
00:38:22,174 --> 00:38:24,844
Yes, if you convince
the rest of the landlords,

613
00:38:24,927 --> 00:38:27,221
the expressway project will be
on the fast track to success.

614
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:31,392
They're fighting each other now.

615
00:38:32,226 --> 00:38:34,312
What are you doing, you jerk?

616
00:38:35,354 --> 00:38:36,355
Hello?

617
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,816
Why are you glaring at me?

618
00:38:38,899 --> 00:38:40,276
Your eyes might pop out.

619
00:38:41,277 --> 00:38:43,988
-What are you doing?
-What do you think? Working, you idiot.

620
00:38:44,071 --> 00:38:46,490
Mr. Song told me
to deal with Seobuk Market!

621
00:38:46,574 --> 00:38:48,576
If it's Mr. Song's business,
no one man is in charge.

622
00:38:48,659 --> 00:38:51,370
Also, you can't take
all the credit forever.

623
00:38:51,454 --> 00:38:53,205
I want to receive credit from him too.

624
00:38:53,289 --> 00:38:55,416
You're not in the position to say that.

625
00:38:55,499 --> 00:38:57,585
-What?
-Do you think I don't know the reason?

626
00:38:58,377 --> 00:39:01,380
Your father owns a piece of land
where the expressway will be built.

627
00:39:01,464 --> 00:39:04,133
Does Mr. Song know about this?

628
00:39:04,216 --> 00:39:05,343
LAND REGISTER

629
00:39:08,554 --> 00:39:11,098
Hey, come on.

630
00:39:12,892 --> 00:39:16,354
We need to make money with these things
while working for assemblymen.

631
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:18,731
We don't get bonuses or extra pay.

632
00:39:18,814 --> 00:39:20,232
We have to do this to...

633
00:39:20,316 --> 00:39:24,028
Why do you pretend like you're so clean?
Everyone else makes extra money like me!

634
00:39:24,111 --> 00:39:25,738
No, it's only you.

635
00:39:25,821 --> 00:39:29,367
-Do you want me to tell Mr. Song myself?
-You little jerk. I'll show you...

636
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:35,539
If you want to keep the benefits you have,
then learn to behave.

637
00:39:47,093 --> 00:39:48,844
Thank you so much for coming.

638
00:39:49,387 --> 00:39:51,347
-Goodbye.
-Sure. Great work.

639
00:39:51,430 --> 00:39:52,431
Thank you.

640
00:39:55,434 --> 00:39:58,270
Sir, please reconsider
the Seoul and Uigwang Expressway project.

641
00:39:58,354 --> 00:39:59,271
Just go ahead with it.

642
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:01,899
That project failed
to pass the validity test.

643
00:40:01,982 --> 00:40:04,276
We can say that we're doing it
to keep the regional balance.

644
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:05,986
Merchants are going to support that, too.

645
00:40:06,070 --> 00:40:09,365
There are less than ten merchants who own
their stores or a piece of land there.

646
00:40:09,448 --> 00:40:11,992
This will cause more serious conflict
between the merchants.

647
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:13,285
I'll meet Mr. Hwang again...

648
00:40:15,079 --> 00:40:16,664
I thought you were smarter than this.

649
00:40:16,747 --> 00:40:18,374
Don't you want to take over Uigwang City?

650
00:40:18,457 --> 00:40:20,418
If you want to do politics,
calculate the numbers.

651
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:22,962
Those ten people
have half of the ballots in Uigwang City.

652
00:40:23,045 --> 00:40:24,922
Then you already know what you should do.

653
00:40:25,714 --> 00:40:29,093
It's easier to do business
after you split up a tightly-knit group.

654
00:40:29,593 --> 00:40:31,053
Don't mind them and keep it going.

655
00:40:31,137 --> 00:40:33,013
Then they will get dispersed naturally.

656
00:40:40,229 --> 00:40:42,690
Are you Mr. Jang Tae-jun?

657
00:40:45,151 --> 00:40:46,777
-Yes.
-Goodness.

658
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:49,447
I heard that you are a competent man.

659
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:51,157
Please help me

660
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:53,784
so that I can keep doing business
at the market

661
00:40:53,868 --> 00:40:55,327
with my grandson.

662
00:40:56,036 --> 00:40:58,372
I ask of you, sir.

663
00:40:58,747 --> 00:41:00,499
Please help us out.

664
00:41:00,583 --> 00:41:03,377
I ask of you. Please.

665
00:41:36,952 --> 00:41:38,829
Don't you want to take over Uigwang City?

666
00:41:38,913 --> 00:41:41,373
If you're going to do politics,
calculate the numbers.

667
00:41:42,541 --> 00:41:45,836
Those ten people have
half of the ballots in Uigwang City.

668
00:42:00,309 --> 00:42:01,477
Let me pour you a glass.

669
00:42:09,902 --> 00:42:12,112
Was it your plan

670
00:42:13,697 --> 00:42:15,115
to ruin the public hearing?

671
00:42:16,033 --> 00:42:17,993
I told you that it wasn't.

672
00:42:18,077 --> 00:42:21,038
Then you should have taken a measure
in advance.

673
00:42:21,121 --> 00:42:22,581
Why did you stand idle?

674
00:42:23,916 --> 00:42:26,961
Those landlords
are also part of Uigwang City.

675
00:42:27,044 --> 00:42:30,214
Of course,
they can claim their legal rights.

676
00:42:32,341 --> 00:42:34,051
Remember the people before the law!

677
00:42:34,134 --> 00:42:37,346
You stopped seeing those people
because you're blinded by political games!

678
00:42:43,727 --> 00:42:44,645
A redevelopment?

679
00:42:45,479 --> 00:42:46,522
It's great.

680
00:42:46,605 --> 00:42:48,732
The town will be cleaner.
There will be broader roads.

681
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:51,318
People who live here
wouldn't want to live like this either.

682
00:42:51,402 --> 00:42:54,655
It's so old and cramped
with barely any space for people to pass.

683
00:42:58,117 --> 00:43:01,704
Do you know why these people
live in such cramped conditions?

684
00:43:03,080 --> 00:43:05,332
Because they feel anxious
unless they live as a group.

685
00:43:05,916 --> 00:43:07,793
They needed to learn how to survive

686
00:43:07,876 --> 00:43:10,671
and live through harsh times together.

687
00:43:10,754 --> 00:43:13,048
Because they don't know
when they will get kicked out.

688
00:43:14,258 --> 00:43:15,259
Do you have to

689
00:43:16,093 --> 00:43:18,971
split them up

690
00:43:19,054 --> 00:43:21,181
and make the lights in the market go out?

691
00:43:25,227 --> 00:43:27,855
My mother also worked in a market
from early morning!

692
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:29,857
Do you think I don't know how they feel?

693
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:31,317
If you know that,

694
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:34,069
you should have dealt with this already!

695
00:43:35,487 --> 00:43:36,614
Damn it.

696
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:42,036
I mean, this isn't something
we can resolve

697
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:46,498
just because you and I know how they feel.

698
00:43:54,006 --> 00:43:54,923
I'm leaving.

699
00:43:56,383 --> 00:43:58,302
I'll take you home.

700
00:43:58,886 --> 00:44:00,387
Forget it. I don't need you.

701
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:02,056
I'm leaving alone.

702
00:44:05,768 --> 00:44:06,935
-Mr. Lee.
-Mr. Lee.

703
00:44:07,936 --> 00:44:09,313
-Are you okay?
-Are you all right?

704
00:44:09,396 --> 00:44:10,230
I'm fine.

705
00:44:15,527 --> 00:44:16,904
Darn it.

706
00:44:18,614 --> 00:44:21,367
-Mr. Lee.
-I'm fine.

707
00:44:21,450 --> 00:44:23,452
I can go alone.

708
00:44:23,744 --> 00:44:25,287
-I'm...
-Mr. Lee.

709
00:44:26,121 --> 00:44:27,748
Gosh, darn it.

710
00:44:28,999 --> 00:44:30,334
You two can go first.

711
00:44:30,417 --> 00:44:32,294
I'll take him home.

712
00:44:32,378 --> 00:44:34,588
-Forget it. I can go by myself.
-Go home.

713
00:44:34,672 --> 00:44:36,465
-I'll be fine.
-Darn you.

714
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:38,967
Hey. Let go of me.

715
00:44:48,977 --> 00:44:51,980
Mr. Jang has nothing to do with this,

716
00:44:52,231 --> 00:44:53,565
does he?

717
00:44:54,274 --> 00:44:55,401
No.

718
00:44:57,653 --> 00:44:58,529
I'm relieved.

719
00:44:59,988 --> 00:45:03,784
I was worried
that he might be behind this.

720
00:45:04,952 --> 00:45:07,830
Why do you like him so much?

721
00:45:12,501 --> 00:45:14,545
Back in high school,

722
00:45:14,795 --> 00:45:17,381
my father was hospitalized
because of an industrial accident.

723
00:45:18,048 --> 00:45:20,342
But he couldn't prove
he was injured at work,

724
00:45:20,426 --> 00:45:22,469
so our family had a difficult time.

725
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:24,805
That's when he helped us out.

726
00:45:25,431 --> 00:45:26,598
He did?

727
00:45:27,182 --> 00:45:28,142
Yes.

728
00:45:29,643 --> 00:45:30,978
It happened long ago,

729
00:45:31,061 --> 00:45:33,397
so I don't think he remembers me.

730
00:45:34,314 --> 00:45:37,818
As much as he helped out our family,

731
00:45:37,901 --> 00:45:40,529
I want to be that someone
for another person.

732
00:45:40,737 --> 00:45:42,531
That's why I came to work here.

733
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:45,367
I'm not competent enough though.

734
00:46:11,935 --> 00:46:13,312
Get some more sleep.

735
00:46:13,395 --> 00:46:15,731
I'll wake you once we're there.

736
00:46:17,858 --> 00:46:19,359
I'll take care of myself.

737
00:46:20,360 --> 00:46:23,405
By the way, what happened to Ms. Kang?

738
00:46:23,489 --> 00:46:24,781
I heard the bill didn't pass.

739
00:46:24,865 --> 00:46:26,658
Is something going on
between her and Mr. Song?

740
00:46:26,742 --> 00:46:29,661
You need to stop caring
about other people's offices.

741
00:46:32,247 --> 00:46:33,499
And

742
00:46:33,999 --> 00:46:36,126
look at your shoes.

743
00:46:36,210 --> 00:46:38,921
-They're so ragged.
-What's so bad about these?

744
00:46:40,005 --> 00:46:41,632
You're the one who should stop caring.

745
00:46:42,257 --> 00:46:43,634
You always nag at me.

746
00:46:49,223 --> 00:46:52,518
You said your mother
also worked in a market.

747
00:46:55,229 --> 00:46:58,690
When my father
lost all of our money in an election,

748
00:46:58,774 --> 00:47:01,693
she worked in a market
from early morning to support me.

749
00:47:02,361 --> 00:47:04,029
Then you must know

750
00:47:05,030 --> 00:47:06,949
how difficult this must be for them.

